            <person xml:id="pers0802">
               <p>Son of a prosperous planter in <placeName>Antigua</placeName>, Francis had taken
                  refuge in <placeName>England</placeName> in disgrace in <date when="1757"
                     >1757</date>. There he and his brother <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers0805.xml"/>Nathaniel</persName> came under the
                  influence of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> and
                  other Methodists and were converted. In <date when="1759">1759</date> the Gilbert
                  brothers returned to <placeName>Antigua</placeName> as evangelists, pioneering
                  Methodist work in the <placeName>West Indies</placeName>. Francis later returned
                  to <placeName>England</placeName> in poor health and died, leaving his wife,
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0804.xml"/>Mary (Leadbetter / née Walsh)
                     Gilbert</persName> a widow. See <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 439; and Vickers,
                     <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 135.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
